      <hedline>
        <hl1>Remnant of Colonialism</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Aaron Fichtelberg letter on May 8 article says Europe's colonial history is at root of Europe's immigration 'problem'</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Europe's Migrant Fears Rend a Spanish Town'' (front page, May 8): Why do countries that made themselves wealthy by plundering the rest of the world become indignant when people from former colonies come to them in search of a decent living?  Anti-immigrant language from the European right cannot hide the fact that Europe's history is at the root of Europe's immigration ''problem.''</p>
        <p>AARON FICHTELBERG  Atlanta, May 8, 2000</p>
      </block>
